ich focuses the sun's rays on it, and fire spurts forth.\", \"from\": 574, \"to\": 692, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the fuel-filled torch\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 609}, {\"ngram\": \"a parabolic mirror\", \"from\": 615, \"to\": 633}, {\"ngram\": \"the sun's rays\", \"from\": 648, \"to\": 662}, {\"ngram\": \"fire spurts\", \"from\": 674, \"to\": 685}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tokyo Olympic rowing gold medalist Stefanos Ntouskos of Greece was the first torchbearer.\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 783, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 694, \"end\": 699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9585523893954844, \"rank\": 0.043204604914793, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 729, \"end\": 746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stefanos Ntouskos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\"}, {\"begin\": 750, \"end\": 756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9849655812359053, \"rank\": 0.015263661967703058, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first torchbearer\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 782}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He handed off to retired French swimmer Laure Manaudou, a three-time medalist at the 2004 Athens Games.\", \"from\": 784, \"to\": 887, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 824, \"end\": 838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laure_Manaudou\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laure Manaudou\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"